myy()

myy=function(Y,X){
  n=nrow(X)
  k=ncol(X)-1
  model=lm(Y~X[,-1])
  r=model$residuals
  coeff=model$coefficients

  SSE=sum(r^2)
  s=sqrt(SSE/(n-(k+1)))
  t=qt(1-alpha/2,n-(k+1))
  pm=c(-1,1)
  
  ci_matrix=matrix(,nrow=n,ncol=2)
  yhat_vector=c()
  for(i in 1:n){
    x=X[i,]

    yhat=0
    for(j in 1:k+1){
      yhat=yhat+(coeff[j]*x[j])
    }

    ci=yhat+pm*t*s*sqrt(1+t(x)%*%solve(t(X)%*%X)%*%x)
    ci_matrix[i,1]=ci[1]
    ci_matrix[i,2]=ci[2]
    yhat_vector=append(yhat_vector,yhat)

  }
  
  
  
  ##### Pairs Plot
  
  pairs_data=X
  pairs_data[,1]=Y

  pairs(pairs_data)
  
  
  
  ###### ggplot of Y vs xi
  # I don't understand what you're asking for here
  
  
  ###### plot of cis and point estimates (x=1:n)
  index=seq(n)
  plot(index,yhat_vector,ylim=c(min(ci_matrix[,1]),max(ci_matrix[,2])))
  for(i in 1:n){
    segments(x0=i,y0=ci_matrix[i,1],y1=ci_matrix[i,2])
  }
  
  
  names(yhat_vector)=seq(n)
  return(list(yhat=yhat_vector,ci=ci_matrix))
}

myl()

myl=function(Y,X,alpha,a,l){
  
  n=nrow(X)
  k=ncol(X)-1
  t=qt(1-alpha/2,n-(k+1))
  pm=c(-1,1)
  
  model=lm(Y~X[,-1])
  coeff=model$coefficients
  
  betahat=matrix(data=coeff,nrow=k+1,ncol=1)
  
  coeff=model$coefficients
  r=model$residuals
  SSE=sum(r^2)
  s=sqrt(SSE/(n-(k+1)))
  
  ci=l+pm*t*s*sqrt(t(a)%*%solve(t(X)%*%X)%*%a)

  pairs(X)
  return(list(ci=ci))
  
}

Task 3

Using Theorem 11.3 page 574, make a function myl() that produces

-(1-\(\alpha\))100% confidence intervals for E(l) given Y, X, \(\alpha\), a, l -a plot using pairs() to show all pairwise plots of the data used in the analysis

myl=function(Y,X,alpha,a,l){
  
  n=nrow(X)
  k=ncol(X)-1
  t=qt(1-alpha/2,n-(k+1))
  pm=c(-1,1)
  
  model=lm(Y~X[,-1])
  coeff=model$coefficients
  
  betahat=matrix(data=coeff,nrow=k+1,ncol=1)
  
  coeff=model$coefficients
  r=model$residuals
  SSE=sum(r^2)
  s=sqrt(SSE/(n-(k+1)))
  
  ci=l+pm*t*s*sqrt(t(a)%*%solve(t(X)%*%X)%*%a)

  pairs(X)
  return(list(ci=ci))
  
}

Task 6

Make a confidence interval for a new y value

#x is a vector with values of x for the new y value
myy=function(x,Y,X){
  n=nrow(X)
  k=ncol(X)-1
  model=lm(Y~X[,-1])
  r=model$residuals
  coeff=model$coefficients
  yhat=coeff[1]
  for(i in 1:k){
    yhat=yhat+(coeff[i+1]*x[i])
  }

  SSE=sum(r^2)
  s=sqrt(SSE/(n-(k+1)))
  t=qt(1-alpha/2,n-(k+1))
  pm=c(-1,1)
  
  ci=yhat+pm*t*s*sqrt(1+t(x)%*%solve(t(X)%*%X)%*%x)
  
  return(list(yhat=yhat,ci=ci))
}

myy=function(Y,X){
  n=nrow(X)
  k=ncol(X)-1
  model=lm(Y~X[,-1])
  r=model$residuals
  coeff=model$coefficients

  SSE=sum(r^2)
  s=sqrt(SSE/(n-(k+1)))
  t=qt(1-alpha/2,n-(k+1))
  pm=c(-1,1)
  
  ci_matrix=matrix(,nrow=n,ncol=2)
  yhat_vector=c()
  for(i in 1:n){
    x=X[i,]

    yhat=0
    for(j in 1:k+1){
      yhat=yhat+(coeff[j]*x[j])
    }

    ci=yhat+pm*t*s*sqrt(1+t(x)%*%solve(t(X)%*%X)%*%x)
    ci_matrix[i,1]=ci[1]
    ci_matrix[i,2]=ci[2]
    yhat_vector=append(yhat_vector,yhat)

  }
  
  
  
  ##### Pairs Plot
  
  pairs_data=X
  pairs_data[,1]=Y

  pairs(pairs_data)
  
  
  
  ###### ggplot of Y vs xi
  # I don't understand what you're asking for here
  
  
  ###### plot of cis and point estimates (x=1:n)
  index=seq(n)
  plot(index,yhat_vector,ylim=c(min(ci_matrix[,1]),max(ci_matrix[,2])))
  for(i in 1:n){
    segments(x0=i,y0=ci_matrix[i,1],y1=ci_matrix[i,2])
  }
  
  
  names(yhat_vector)=seq(n)
  return(list(yhat=yhat_vector,ci=ci_matrix))
}
